      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:6:71:2",
      "text": [
        " مَنْ لَمْ يُرِدْ مِنَّا الْحَلْوَاءَ أَرَادَ الشَّرَابَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Ali Bin Abu Hamza, from Abu Baseer, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The one who does not want (to eat) the sweet dishes from us, wants the (sweet) drinks’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "2. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad from Ali ibn abu Hamzah from abu Basir who has said the following: “If one of us does not want al-Halwa’ he wants drink (which is sweet).”’ "
        ]
      }
